## Quick Start

### Option 1: Daytona (Recommended)

```bash
# Clone and deploy to a new Daytona sandbox
git clone git@github.com:${GITHUB_OWNER}/${SYSTEM_NAME}.git
cd ${SYSTEM_NAME}
chmod +x setup.sh
./setup.sh
```

### Option 2: Local

```bash
# Prerequisites: Node.js 22+, OpenClaw installed
git clone git@github.com:${GITHUB_OWNER}/${SYSTEM_NAME}.git
cd ${SYSTEM_NAME}

# Configure environment
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your credentials

# Copy to OpenClaw workspace
cp -r . ~/.openclaw/workspace/

# Start
openclaw start
```

